    <H1>Overview</H1><DIV class="s1">
      <P>
        Jesktop supports different skins for the decoration of frames, fonts, colors and iconography.
      </P>
    </DIV>
    <H1>Detailed</H1><DIV class="s1">
      <P>
        By Skin we mean the decoration that surrounds individual frames, the style and colors of widgets. We allow skin changing through applications that implement a Decorator interface.  These applications will be Jesktop only (not dual mode), but the toolkits they use might be quite independent of Jesktop. At this stage we have the following:
      </P>
      <UL>
        <LI>
          Default Decorator.  Metal Look and Feel and small icons for application frames.
        </LI>
        <LI>
          Test Decorator.  Choice of Metal or Motif look and feel, Choice of small of Big icons for application frames.  <A href="http://www.jesktopapps.sourceforge.net">See www.jesktopapps.sourceforge.net</A>
        </LI>
        <LI>
          OYOAHA Decorator.  Multiple choices of look and feel.  The license for this is a bit unclear and Jesktop uses the compiled jar.  <A href="http://www.jesktopapps.sourceforge.net">See www.jesktopapps.sourceforge.net</A> and <A href="http://www.oyoaha.com">www.oyoaha.com</A>
        </LI>
        <LI>
          Skin look and feel Decorator.  Again, multiple choices of look and feel.  The license for this is Apache-alike.  <A href="http://www.jesktopapps.sourceforge.net">See www.jesktopapps.sourceforge.net</A> and <A href="http://www.l2fprod.com">www.l2fprod.com</A>.  Mac, Windows, Beos, Aqua and XP-Luna look and feels are provided.
        </LI>
      </UL>
    </DIV>
